        .features
          %p= "You can find MapQuest Travel Blogs on <a href='https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mapquest-travel-blogs/id602353608?mt=8' target='_blank'>the App Store</a> and its <a href='//travelblogs.mapquest.com' target='_blank'>offical site</a>. You can learn more about MapQuest Travel Blogs on <a href='//finance.yahoo.com/news/mapquest-introduces-free-travel-blogs-205300683.html' target='_blank'>Yahoo!</a>, <a href='//thenextweb.com/insider/2013/02/28/mapquest-touts-its-everlater-acquisition-launches-free-travel-blogs-for-the-web-and-ios/' target='_blank'>The Next Web</a>, <a href='//www.tuaw.com/2013/03/11/mapquest-travel-blogs-ios-app-capture-and-share-your-journeys/' target='_blank'>TUAW</a>, and <a href='//blog.aol.com/2013/02/28/mapquest-ecosystem-expands-through-launch-of-travel-blogs/' target='_blank'>the Aol. Blog</a>."
        .credit
          %p= "I worked on the MapQuest Travel Blogs app with <a href='//tivona.me' target='_blank'>Devon Tivona</a> and the <a href='//company.mapquest.com/careers/' target='_blank'>MapQuest Mobile Team</a> in 2012 and 2013 while at <a href='//monospacecollective.com' target='_blank'>Monospace</a> as client work for <a href='http://company.mapquest.com' target='_blank'>MapQuest</a>/<a href='//corp.aol.com' target='_blank'>Aol</a>."
        .footnote
          %p= "The MapQuest Travel Blogs app was originally the Everlater Travel Blogs app, written during my time at <a href='//everlater.com' target='_blank'>Everlater Inc.</a> from 2011–2012. Everlater was acquired by MapQuest/Aol. in 2012 and the Everlater app was subsequently integrated into MapQuest as the MapQuest Travel Blogs app."

